<HEADLINE>
<P>
CONTROVERSY OVER HAYDEN AND 'BIG GREEN' 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
After reading the Hayden initiative, Proposition 128, I have come to the 
conclusion that too many complex and important subjects are thrown together in 
this one measure. 
</P>
<P>
Once the thoughtful voter sifts through the 16,000-word document, it becomes 
painfully clear that matters such as saving our redwood trees, food safety, the 
greenhouse effect on the entire planet, carbon dioxide emissions, car and home 
air-conditioning systems, water-quality standards and energy supplies cannot be 
addressed in a single initiative. 
</P>
<P>
Then, when one realizes that the $3-billion price tag attached to Hayden's 
initiative will be placed on the backs of the taxpayers of California, the 
voter really has to be alarmed. 
</P>
<P>
SARA DIVITO HARDMAN 
</P>
<P>
Tarzana 
</P>
</TEXT>
