DIGEST /LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: FREEWAY'S TRUCK LANES TO BE CLOSED FOR REPAIRS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The truck lanes of the northbound Golden State Freeway will be closed this 
weekend while workers repair a collapsed drainage pipe five feet below the 
pavement, the state Department of Transportation announced Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
The lanes will close about 10 p.m. Friday, and trucks will be routed onto the 
regular traffic lanes. The truck route, a quarter of a mile north of the 
Foothill Freeway interchange, should be reopened by 1 p.m. Monday, Caltrans 
officials said. 
</P>
