<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO SPORTS ET CETERA: UC SAN DIEGO DEFEATS PLNC IN MEN'S SOCCER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Jarret Stevenson and Chris Romey scored goals as UC San Diego defeated host 
Point Loma Nazarene, 3-0, Wednesday in men's soccer. 
</P>
<P>
The Tritons' other goal hit off a Point Loma Nazarene player. 
</P>
<P>
UCSD improved to 2-1. Point Loma Nazarene fell to 2-1. 
</P>
<P>
WOMEN'S VOLLEYBALL 
</P>
<P>
Eighteenth-ranked San Diego State, the University of San Diego and U.S. 
International open play tonight in second Asics Grand Prix tournament at SDSU's 
Peterson Gym and the Physical Education Gym. 
</P>
<P>
The tournament, which includes eight teams, will be broken into two pools for 
matches today and Friday. The championship-round games will be played Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
SDSU and USD are in Pool A along with Hofstra and Arizona State. Pepperdine, UC 
Santa Barbara, Providence and USIU are in Pool B. 
</P>
<P>
SURFING 
</P>
<P>
Despite losing a heat to Florida's Kelly Slater, Oceanside's David Barr 
advanced into the fourth round of the $100,000 Body Glove Surf Bout 
competition. Three-time U.S. champion Mike Lambresi of Oceanside is seeded and 
begins surfing today. 
</P>
