<P>
WESTSIDE DIGEST: BEVERLY HILLS; 
</P>
<P>
FUND-RAISER FOR EXODUS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Home meetings in the Beverly Hills-West Los Angeles area have raised more than 
$2 million toward Operation Exodus, the Jewish community's fund-raising drive 
to help emigrants from the Soviet Union, a spokesman said. 
</P>
<P>
Richard Gunther, co-chair of the local campaign, said Los Angeles-area donors 
have come up with almost $22 million toward a goal of $36 million. 
</P>
<P>
"The home parlor meetings have been so successful because individual 
contributors recognize the peril of the Soviet Jews and are responding in a 
heartfelt way," Gunther said. 
</P>
<P>
Funds raised help pay for transportation from the Soviet Union, housing, job 
training, language classes and other relocation expenses. 
</P>
