<P>
KUWAITI DELICACY GOES FOR $2.7 MILLION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
ABU DHABI, United Arab Emirates 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The wife of the ruler of the United Arab Emirates has paid $2.7 million for a 
plate of Kuwaiti food. 
</P>
<P>
Shaika Fatima, wife of Emirates President Sheik Zayed ibn Sultan al Nuhayan, 
picked up the multimillion-dollar morsel at a charity cook-in Tuesday to raise 
money for Kuwaiti families displaced by Iraq's Aug. 2 invasion. 
</P>
<P>
The baid al qata (mashed eggs and sand grouse), presented in an aluminum foil 
container, are oval dumplings, a traditional Kuwaiti delicacy regarded as a 
good omen. 
</P>
<P>
Fatima cried tears of joy at her acquisition, according to the English-language 
Khaleej Times. 
</P>
