<P>
WATER-SAVING KITS OFFERED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
To help residents conserve water, the city will distribute 5,000 kits 
containing devices that restrict water flow in faucets, toilets and shower 
heads. 
</P>
<P>
The kits are available for free at City Hall, 116 E. Foothill Blvd. 
</P>
<P>
Since May, when the City Council approved a resolution asking residents to 
reduce water usage by 10%, there has been a reduction of more than 7%. 
</P>
