<P>
NEW CANCER SUPPORT CENTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Emotional and psychological support for cancer patients and their families is 
being offered free at the Wellness Community Foothills, 100 N. Hill Ave., which 
opened Aug. 23. 
</P>
<P>
More than 300 clients are expected to be served each month by the nonprofit 
agency, Executive Director Anne Kennedy said. 
</P>
<P>
The Pasadena clinic is affiliated with eight Wellness Community offices 
operating in other parts of the country. Services provided include relaxation 
techniques and group therapy. 
