<P>
SIDEWALK REPAIR PLANNED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A $5.5-million, two-year residential sidewalk repair program will begin in 
October in Northwest Pasadena as part of the city's six-year Infrastructure 
Repair Program. 
</P>
<P>
Slated for repairs are sections of broken sidewalks and driveways with gaps or 
rises of an inch or more. About 250,000 square feet of pavement in front of 
homes and apartments of less than four units will be repaired. 
</P>
