<HEADLINE>
<P>
LOCAL STOREHOUSES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
People interested in local history might start at one of the following places: 
</P>
<P>
* Ventura County Museum of History and Art, 100 E. Main St., Ventura, 653-0323. 
Has a display area, upstairs library and a big stuffed bear that overlooks 
both. 
</P>
<P>
* County Cultural Heritage Board, County Government Center, 800 S. Victoria 
Ave., Ventura, 654-3967. It has information on property history and local 
landmarks. 
</P>
<P>
* Foster Library, 651 E. Main St., Ventura, 648-2715. Along with reference and 
historical work, the county library has information on tracing genealogy. 
</P>
<P>
* Naval Construction Battalion Center Museum, or Seabee Museum, just past the 
gate at Ventura Road and Sunkist Street, Port Hueneme, 982-5163. 
</P>
<P>
* Ojai Valley Museum, 109 S. Montgomery St., Ojai, 646-2290. 
</P>
<P>
* Pleasant Valley Historical Society Museum, 720 N. Las Posas Road, Camarillo, 
482-3660. 
</P>
<P>
* Stagecoach Inn Museum, 51 S. Ventu Park Road, Newbury Park, 498-9441. 
</P>
<P>
* Strathearn Historical Park, 137 Strathearn Place, Simi Valley, 526-6453. 
</P>
<P>
* Unocal Oil Museum, 1003 E. Main St., Santa Paula, 933-0076. 
</P>
</TEXT>
