253 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
SCHOOL REPORT; 
</P>
<P>
NEW SCHOOLS JOIN NORTH COUNTY RANKS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The oldest school in North County is in Spencer Valley. Opened in 1877, the 
Spencer Valley School has 31 students in two classrooms. 
</P>
<P>
The newest schools in North County are in Fallbrook, San Marcos, Carlsbad and 
Poway. Opening their doors for the first time this school year: 
</P>
<P>
Live Oaks Elementary School 
</P>
<P>
(Grades: 4-6) 
</P>
<P>
1978 Reche Road, Fallbrook 
</P>
<P>
723-6701 
</P>
<P>
Students: 600 
</P>
<P>
Teachers: 21 
</P>
<P>
Paloma Elementary 
