<HEADLINE>
<P>
SCHOOL REPORT; 
</P>
<P>
BELL TOLLS NEW YEAR FOR SCHOOLS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By This report was compiled by staff writers Caroline Lemke and Mark Stencel. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
More than 148,000 North County elementary, middle and high school students 
heeded the peal of the school bell earlier this week and headed back to public 
school classrooms. They were met there by 11,031 teachers armed with chalk, 
textbooks and computers. 
</P>
<P>
On these pages is a compilation of facts about the 26 school districts in North 
County. 
</P>
