<HEADLINE>
<P>
OXNARD'S MEGGS TAKES LBCC JOB 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JEFF RILEY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Long Beach City College officials said late Wednesday that Oxnard College Coach 
Lindsay Meggs has been hired as the school's baseball coach, filling a vacancy 
created when Ken Gaylord resigned earlier in the day. 
</P>
<P>
Meggs, who was an assistant at Cal Lutheran in 1989, led the Condors to a 14-22 
record last season, his first at Oxnard. Oxnard finished 10th among 11 teams in 
the Western State Conference. 
</P>
<P>
Gaylord, who coached at Long Beach City College for six seasons, accepted a 
similar position at Cerritos College. Oxnard officials were unavailable for 
comment regarding a replacement for Meggs. JEFF RILEY 
</P>
