<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: STUDENT PLEADS NOT GUILTY TO MURDER OF 
TEACHER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 19-year-old nursing student pleaded not guilty Wednesday to charges of 
first-degree murder and attempted murder in a shooting that left a teacher dead 
and and two others wounded at the West Covina vocational school she attended, 
officials said. 
</P>
<P>
Lisa Villela, who originally was charged with being an accessory to the Aug. 16 
attack, was scheduled to return Sept. 27 for a preliminary hearing at Citrus 
Municipal Court in West Covina. 
</P>
<P>
The Duarte woman, who is pregnant with her third child, is accused of driving 
the getaway car for her boyfriend and the suspected triggerman, Martin Meza. 
Meza, a Mexican citizen, is being tried on murder charges in Mexicali, where he 
and Villela were arrested after the shooting. 
</P>
