<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: BRADLEY FINED $2,000 FOR UNREPORTED 
DONATION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Los Angeles Mayor Tom Bradley was fined $2,000 Wednesday by the state Fair 
Political Practices Commission, which said he failed to disclose receiving 
$1,800 from a contract-seeking company while serving on a local transportation 
commission. 
</P>
<P>
The FPPC said that Bradley, while an appointed member of the Los Angeles County 
Transportation Commission, chaired the meeting at which the panel voted to 
award a contract for an environmental study to a local firm, Gruen Associates. 
</P>
<P>
The study was aimed at detailing the impact of light rail service routes on the 
San Fernando Valley. 
</P>
<P>
"Since he chaired the particular meeting in which this contract was voted upon, 
he participated in the decision," the FPPC said. 
</P>
<P>
Before the Feb. 11, 1987, vote, Bradley's political campaign had received three 
checks from Gruen in 1986 -- one for $600 in March, another for $200 in August 
and a third for $1,000 in October. 
</P>
</TEXT>
