ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: MISSION VIEJO; 
</P>
<P>
PARKS-RECREATION REPLACEMENT NAMED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By FRANK MESSINA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A longtime South County resident has been named the city's new parks and 
recreation director. 
</P>
<P>
Kelly Doyle, who has lived in San Clemente for the past 11 years, will take 
over the job from Wayne Lowery, who resigned earlier this summer. 
</P>
<P>
Doyle, who has 15 years' experience working for parks and recreation 
departments in San Clemente and Corona, will begin his new job on Monday. "The 
city is fortunate to attract someone of Mr. Doyle's caliber," said City Manager 
Fred Sorsabal. "His reputation is excellent and he has many years of parks and 
recreation experience." 
</P>
<P>
Doyle holds a master's degree in public administration and has done graduate 
work in recreation administration.FRANK MESSINA 
</P>
</TEXT>
