<HEADLINE>
<P>
VOLLEYBALL SERIES BEGINS FIRST OF SIX NIGHTS AT FORUM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By PETE THOMAS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Professional volleyball players from indoors and out will get together for six 
nights of team cup play this month, beginning tonight at 7 at the Forum. 
</P>
<P>
A total of 32 players -- including two-time Olympians Karch Kiraly, Steve 
Timmons and Dave Saunders, as well as beach volleyball stars Sinjin Smith and 
Randy Stoklos -- will play on the four teams of six players and two alternates 
competing in a round-robin format that concludes Sept. 23. 
</P>
<P>
The other games will be Sunday; Tuesday; Wednesday, Sept. 19, and Saturday, 
Sept. 22. 
</P>
<P>
Sponsorship has grown since the event began five years ago. The $110,000 in 
prize money this season is up 10% from the first year, but is still well below 
the $200,000 in prize money offered by the Assn. of Volleyball Professionals' 
final event on its beach tour this summer. 
</P>
<P>
"I would like to be offering more prize money," said Jeannie Buss, event 
coordinator. "But the players have to understand that we can't do that until 
we're making money." 
</P>
<P>
Timmons, who is married to Buss, said: "It's real important for volleyball to 
stay visible between the Olympics and the beach seasons." PETE THOMAS 
</P>
</TEXT>
