<P>
THE SIDELINES; 
</P>
<P>
NFL TO STUDY DICKERSON'S STATUS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
INDIANAPOLIS 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The NFL will take a look at the Eric Dickerson-Indianapolis Colts feud. 
</P>
<P>
Dickerson, who was placed on the Colts' non-football injury list and suspended 
by the team, is scheduled to meet with NFL counsel Jay Moyer on Sept. 17 in New 
York. League spokesman Greg Aiello said a Colts' representative could also be 
present at the meeting. 
</P>
<P>
Dickerson, who recently refused to have his injured left hamstring examined by 
a Colts' physician, claims that he is healthy and never should have been placed 
on the non-football injury list. Because of the Colts' moves, Dickerson 
virtually forfeits more than $450,000 in salary. 
</P>
<P>
Dickerson missed the entire preseason. 
</P>
</TEXT>
